===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|vertebra||joint|lang=la}}, from ''[[vertere]]'', "to turn". Having multiple [[vertebrae]] (plural of vertebra) in one's backbone instead of having a single bone or solid spine, allows for the movement of the body with bends and turns. Hence meaning 1.

